  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: How to Apply -->
  <section class="section section--cream" id="how-to-apply">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <span class="section-label">Application Process</span>
      <h2 class="section-title text-balance">How to Apply for a China Green Card: Step-by-Step</h2>
      <p>Applications are submitted to the <strong>Exit-Entry Administration Bureau (PSB)</strong> in the district where you live or work. Requirements differ slightly by city — Shanghai, Shenzhen, and Beijing each have local variations. Here is the universal process.</p>

      <ol class="steps-list" role="list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Determine Your Pathway</h4>
            <p>Identify which eligibility category applies to you (professional, spouse, investor, talent). Your pathway determines which documents you need and which PSB office handles your case. Mixing documents from multiple categories does not strengthen an application.</p>
            <span class="step-tip" aria-label="Pro tip">
              <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="5.5" stroke="#9a3412"></circle><path d="M6 4v3M6 8.5h.01" stroke="#9a3412" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg>
              Most expats miss this — choosing the wrong pathway causes rejection on technicality.
            </span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Complete a Medical Health Check</h4>
            <p>Book an appointment at an approved International Travel Healthcare Center. You will be tested for infectious diseases, chest X-ray, and general health markers. The certificate is only valid for a short period, so time this carefully relative to your application.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Obtain a Foreign Criminal Record Check</h4>
            <p>Get an apostilled criminal record check from your home country (US, UK, Australia, EU). Since China joined the international apostille agreement, a local apostille is sufficient — no additional notarization is required. Have it officially translated by a certified translation office.</p>
            <span class="step-tip">
              <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="5.5" stroke="#9a3412"></circle><path d="M6 4v3M6 8.5h.01" stroke="#9a3412" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg>
              Processing from the US FBI can take 6–10 weeks. Start this first.
            </span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Assemble Financial &amp; Marital Proof</h4>
            <p>Depending on your pathway: gather salary slips and tax records (professional track), a Fixed-Term Deposit Certificate of 200,000 RMB notarized by a Public Notary Office (spouse track), or investment certificates and company financial statements (investor track). Proof of marriage must be notarized and, if issued abroad, less than 6 months old.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">5</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Prepare Your Residence &amp; Presence Evidence</h4>
            <p>You must demonstrate your physical presence in China for the required consecutive years. Prepare stamped passport copies covering the full period, plus a current rental contract with at least 6 months remaining or property ownership documents.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">6</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Write a Personal Statement (Recommended)</h4>
            <p>Not universally required, but some PSB offices (especially outside tier-1 cities) request a multi-page personal statement explaining your background, reasons for applying, and ties to China. Always prepare this — better to have it ready than scramble after submission.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">7</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Submit In Person at the PSB (Appointment Required)</h4>
            <p>Submit all documents in person at the Exit-Entry Administration office in your district. Walk-in submissions are not accepted — book an appointment in advance. Expect to be asked for additional supplementary documents on the day. Pay the application fee of 1,500 RMB at submission.</p>
            <span class="step-tip">
              <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="5.5" stroke="#9a3412"></circle><path d="M6 4v3M6 8.5h.01" stroke="#9a3412" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg>
              Bring originals and photocopies of everything, plus extra passport photos.
            </span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">8</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Wait for the Decision</h4>
            <p>The PSB has up to 6 months to decide on applications, though in practice it varies by city and pathway. The decision is made by a separate authority from the one that receives applications. You may be contacted for additional information during this period.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">9</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Collect Your Card &amp; Pay Final Fee</h4>
            <p>If approved, return to the PSB to collect your Permanent Residence Permit. Pay the card issuance fee of 300 RMB. Your green card is now valid and active.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <div class="cta-box-text">
          <h3>Worried about making a procedural mistake?</h3>
          <p>We handle the full application process on your behalf — from document checklist to PSB submission — so your application is filed correctly the first time.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/consultation" class="btn btn-primary" style="white-space:nowrap;">Get Expert Help</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: Documents -->
  <section class="section" id="documents">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Checklist</span>
      <h2 class="section-title text-balance">Documents You Must Prepare</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">This is the most common cause of rejection and delay. Missing or improperly authenticated documents will stall your application. The exact list varies by pathway and city — below covers the universal requirements and the most common pathway-specific additions.</p>

      <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px; font-size:1.1rem;">Required for All Pathways</h3>
      <div class="doc-grid" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
        <div class="doc-card required"><span class="doc-badge req">Required</span><h4>Valid Passport</h4><p>Original plus copies of all pages. Must have sufficient validity remaining.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card required"><span class="doc-badge req">Required</span><h4>Current Residence Permit</h4><p>Your existing valid Chinese visa or temporary residence permit.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card required"><span class="doc-badge req">Required</span><h4>Health Check Certificate</h4><p>From an approved International Travel Healthcare Center. Only valid for a limited period.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card required"><span class="doc-badge req">Required</span><h4>Foreign Criminal Record Check</h4><p>Apostilled and officially translated. FBI for Americans; DBS/ACRO for UK nationals.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card required"><span class="doc-badge req">Required</span><h4>Proof of Current Residence</h4><p>Rental contract with at least 6 months remaining, or property ownership title.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card required"><span class="doc-badge req">Required</span><h4>Passport Photos</h4><p>Multiple recent photos to Chinese government specifications. Bring extras.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px; font-size:1.1rem;">Professional Track (Pathway A)</h3>
      <div class="doc-grid" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Employment Contract</h4><p>Current contract with your Chinese employer, meeting the salary threshold.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Tax Payment Records</h4><p>Annual personal income tax records for the prior 4 years, meeting the minimum tax-paid threshold.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Work Permit Certificate</h4><p>Your foreign expert certificate or work permit from the relevant authority.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Passport Entry/Exit Stamps</h4><p>Copies of all pages showing 4 years of 6-months-per-year physical presence.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px; font-size:1.1rem;">Spouse Track (Pathway C)</h3>
      <div class="doc-grid" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Marriage Certificate</h4><p>If married in China or Hong Kong: straightforward. If abroad: notarized copy less than 6 months old.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Chinese Spouse's Hukou &amp; ID</h4><p>Household registration book and national ID card of your Chinese spouse.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card conditional"><span class="doc-badge cond">Track-Specific</span><h4>Bank Deposit Certificate</h4><p>200,000 RMB Fixed-Term Deposit Certificate, notarized at a Public Notary Office. Takes 4–5 working days.</p></div>
        <div class="doc-card"><span class="doc-badge opt">Sometimes Required</span><h4>Personal Statement Letter</h4><p>Multi-page statement on your background and reasons for applying. Required by some PSB offices.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="alert" role="note">
        <span class="alert-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M10 1L1 17h18L10 1z" stroke="#c2410c" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
            <path d="M10 8v4M10 14h.01" stroke="#c2410c" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <span class="alert-text"><strong>Common rejection trigger:</strong> Documents issued abroad must be apostilled and officially translated by a certified agency. Translations from Taobao vendors may be accepted in some cities but rejected in others — certified agencies provide greater security.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

