        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon stop" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7.5" stroke="#dc2626"></circle><path d="M5 8h6" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="limit-text"><h4>No Military Service Eligibility</h4><p>You cannot serve in the Chinese military, nor are you subject to military obligations.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon warn" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M8 1.5L1 13.5h14L8 1.5z" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M8 7v3M8 11.5h.01" stroke="#d97706" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="limit-text"><h4>Physical Presence Requirement</h4><p>You must not be absent from China for more than 12 consecutive months or your permit may be cancelled.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon warn" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M8 1.5L1 13.5h14L8 1.5z" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M8 7v3M8 11.5h.01" stroke="#d97706" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="limit-text"><h4>Subject to Chinese Law Fully</h4><p>Green card holders are fully subject to Chinese law and regulations, including exit ban provisions if involved in legal proceedings.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon warn" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M8 1.5L1 13.5h14L8 1.5z" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M8 7v3M8 11.5h.01" stroke="#d97706" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="limit-text"><h4>Not a Pathway to Citizenship</h4><p>China does not offer general naturalisation to foreigners. The green card is the endpoint of the residency system, not a citizenship stepping stone.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon warn" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M8 1.5L1 13.5h14L8 1.5z" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M8 7v3M8 11.5h.01" stroke="#d97706" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="limit-text"><h4>Some Restricted Industries</h4><p>Certain government and sensitive-sector roles remain restricted for non-citizens even with a green card.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon stop" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7.5" stroke="#dc2626"></circle><path d="M5 8h6" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="limit-text"><h4>Revocable Under Certain Conditions</h4><p>The permit can be revoked for criminal activity, extended absence, or if the original qualifying conditions (e.g. marriage) cease to apply.</p></div>
